==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lambent
<hw>Lam"bent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lambens</ets>, <ets>-enlis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>lambere</ets> to
lick; akin to <ets>lap</ets>. See <er>Lap</er> to drink by
licking.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Playing on the surface; touching
lightly; gliding over.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>lambent</xex> flame.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Dryden.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>lambent</xex> style.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Beaconsfield.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Twinkling or gleaming; fickering.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>lambent</xex> purity of the stars.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>W.
Irving.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lambertia</ent>⟦br⟧
